					<div class="commentbody">"Normal" apple cider is just mediocre juice from mediocre apples.  It has no complexity nor depth the way cider apples do.  You deride "hard cider" because you don't know what a cider apple can do.  Fermented and aged cider apple juice is complex and subtley flavored, unlike "koolaid" apple-juice-cider.  Kids like it, but not mature adults who have a developed sense of taste.<br />
Patrick</div>
