					<div class="commentheading">On February 03, 2007 at 02:06 AM, BigbirdMD (guest) said...</div>
					<div class="commentsubject">Subject: <span>my recipe</span><br /></div>
					<div class="commentbody">I have never used peppercorns (but I think I'll try next batch), but instead use 10-15 whole allspice.  I like cinnamon, so for a half-gallon, I use about 8 sticks and about 15 whole cloves.  The surface peel of half an orange goes in next and the whole half gallon simmers in the crock pot with the lid off.  The mixture gradually concentrates and my home then smells of spiced cider and the winter dry air becomes more comfortable.  <br />
<br />
Because I have diabetes, I make a cup of sugar-free commercially marketed spiced cider and add about a quarter cup of my highly spiced concentrate to bring it up to speed, then add a bit of extra lemon or lime juice and sweetener to taste.<br />
<br />
Rob McCormick, MD</div>
