					<div class="commentheading">On December 02, 2007 at 04:57 AM, Ugali (guest) said...</div>
					<div class="commentsubject">Subject: <span>cider v. juice</span><br /></div>
					<div class="commentbody">Big differences in cider v. juice ... cider is less filtered, and unpasteurized (hence its tendency to ferment if not drunk in short order, and the fact that it is sold refrigerated).  Juice is more filtered, pasteurized, and vacuum sealed, and tends to have additives (sugar, water, preservatives, etc).  One voter for cider in this camp!</div>
